10/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- On Monday (9 June), King Juan Carlos I of Spain expressed his country's strong support for Bulgaria's aspirations to join NATO and the EU. 
He also praised the country's achievements in reforms and development and its contribution to building a more solid and united Europe. 
His comments came during an official dinner held in his and Queen Sofia's honour by Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov. 
(Dnevnik, Trud, 24 Chassa - 10/06/03; BTA, BNT - 09/06/03)
